They found no remarkable differences between the mean M∗ of
obscured and unobscured AGNs. On the other hand, Lanzuisi
et al. (2017), used approximately 700 X-ray selected AGNs, in
the COSMOS field in the redshift range 0.1 < z < 4, and found
that unobscured AGNs tend to have lower M∗ than obscured
sources. However, they considered as X-ray absorbed sources
with NH > 1022 cm−2. To be consistent with Lanzuisi et al.
