to have lower M∗ than their obscured counterparts. However, in
their analysis they divided their sample into type 1 and type 2
AGNs based on their optical spectra, morphologies, and variabil-
ity. Thus, the disagreement with our results could be attributed to
the different method applied in the characterisation of a source
as obscured/unobscured."
