"Our findings agree with most previous studies (Merloni et al.
2014; Lanzuisi et al. 2017; Zou et al. 2019). On the other hand,
Chen et al. (2015) used AGN from the Böotes field and claimed
that type 2 sources have higher IR star formation luminosities (a
proxy of star formation) by a factor of ∼ 2 than type 1. How-
